<br>
Now, to address your absolutely ridiculous claims. You know what, yea, we warriors do want realistic combat setup. Why; because that way we'd be on a separate mitigation table, instead of sharing one with all other plate classes. (hint, when warriors have the same max damage/hit as most other classes; you've got a problem).<br>
<br>
Another hint; monk damage avoidance is already better than plate classes. However, you shared the same defensive tables as us, all the while parsing out 2x our damage (yes, I have seen parses out of NToV, regular mobs and ssra to validate my point. I've actually seen a monk parse out close to 3x the damage of a non-tanking warrior). Not to mention that the HP gap between monks and warriors was decreasing percentage-wise (thanks 125hp all/all items with &lt; 1.0 weight). <br>
<br>
You wanna talk realism; explain to me how a pajama-wearing man with a stick can do 2-3 times the damage of a class which, by Verants own definition is supposed to be &quot;a master of armed combat.&quot; Furthermore, the monk is still avoiding damage better, holding agro better (sustained DPS holds agro very well), while remaining on the same mitigation tables. THe monk also has a 25% heal every 6 minutes and this funky little ability called FEign Death, which can effectively drop them from the agro list. All the while, the monk gives up about 1500hp and doesn't have a 3-min wonder disc (although monks do have Stonestance). PLease explain the realism behind any of this.<br>
<br>
Let me reiterate, monks were already better at avoidance, but shared the same mitigation tables. This is not realism, although I'm sure it will heavily damage your ubar Velks soloing ability; where you could solo better than ANY class if you had epic and fungi. <br>
<br>
Let me summarise, in a manner befitting for you. Monk not warrior. You are bad troll. Go away.  <p><center><p><font size = 3 colo = "blue"><b>Wilhelmm D'Averam<br>Warlord of the Apocalypse</b></font></p></center>

