<br>
My theory is that some of the really lame trolling flames at MB supposedly written by warriors are actually written by monks pretending to be warriors in order to make warriors look stupid.  I think that likewise, some of the totally lame posts made here that are supposedly by monks are actually by warriors who are trying to make monks look stupid.   <br>
<br>
Why?  It just boggles the mind how lame some of these posts are.  I am talking about people that spew a constant stream of abuse (usually full of spelling and punctuation errors).  They won't discuss the issues.  They merely launch a barrage of insults at their target, as if that would change anybody's mind on the subject.  <br>
<br>
As far as any particular class being full of morons, I got news for you.  It doesn't take a rocket scientist to play any of the classes in EQ.  A 12 year-old kid of average intelligence could do a halfway decent job of playing any class in EQ.  That includes warriors.  That includes monks.  I wish I could say that being a monk means being a cut above the rest, but it doesn't.  Being a warrior doesn't mean that either.  Your class in EQ doesn't define your intelligence, your personal character, or anything about you.<br>
<br>
I can't remember if it was on this thread or not, but someone mentioned that in the long, marathon length encounters that a melee could hit auto-attack and go afk to take a nap or order pizza.  That is just silly.  If I did that more than a couple of times and anyone noticed, I would be banned from raiding with my guild and possibly de-guilded.  I would be in trouble the very first time it happened if I got caught.  It's one of the cardinal rules of raiding that you NEVER go AFK on a raid without permission.  If you do, your wife better be having a baby or something of similar urgency must be going on.  <br>
<br>
I don't trust Verant.  When Verant discovers that they can't turn a screw with a hammer, their solution is to get a bigger hammer.  On the plus side, they actually used to be much worse about that than they are these days.  <br>
<br>
As some other monk predicted, I think that they will likely nerf monks too much on this patch and then gradually, over a period of months, bring them up to a tolerable level.  Meanwhile, it will really, really suck to be a monk or someone that depends on monks.<br>
<br>
So what if some of you have had some bad experiences with monks?  Who gives a crap!  Grow up!  I have had some bad experiences with monks myself.  I recall when I was camping an area in a dungeon where I was at the end of a dead-end tunnel.  Another monk and his shaman girlfriend moved into the next room in the tunnel, &quot;locking&quot; me into that room.  Every pull I attempted to bring past them, they took for themselves and accused me of kill stealling.  When I attempted to camp the room past them, they did the same.  I could have fought it out with them, but I just left.  I have also had bad experiences with warriors.  I recall the ogre warrior that stood in a tunnel, blocking my escape to the zoneline while FD failed on me three times in a row.  He just stood there and roleplayed a dumb ogre while I was dying and begging him to move.  As I went unconcious and into an overhead view I saw him say, &quot;Me go now.&quot; and turn and zone.  Do I hate monks because of this?  NO!  Do I hate warriors because of this?  NO!  None of you are impressing anybody with your stories about why you hate &lt;insert class&gt;.  We've all met people from a variety of classes that did us wrong.  I could tell you about this cleric I once met . . . . <br>
<br>
I can almost guarantee that whatever happens, this patch will not be final.  Verant will either: (A)  make things too easy, such as making it possible for one group to kill all of NToV, catch their mistake within 30 minutes of it going live and fix it in an emergency patch hours before I log on that day, or (B) totally screw up one or more classes, say it's working just as intended, then fix it six months later.<br>
<br>
P.S.  That monk that screwed me over ended up trying to get into my guild months later.  Muahahahahah!!!!  What goes around comes around!  <br>
<br>
P.P.S.  Okay, I have to confess, I didn't remember what the guy had done until after he had already been rejected because of what he did to another guildmate, but still, it felt pretty sweet!<br>
 <p>Argfeld<BR>
Level 58 Monk<BR>
