</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2F2F4F><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/uaragirlancot.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Aragir Lancot</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>is a Formidable Opponent</span><br>  Posts: 111<br> <font color=#FF0000>(10/15/02 6:20:36 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthetavern.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1386.topic&index=112>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: An open letter to Warriors from a Monk...</span><hr size=1> Something I've wondered lately...<br>
<br>
Monks are better tanks than warriors under specific circumstances, right?  When their mitigation AC = warrior mitigation AC, AND the mob isn't hitting for completely unreasonable damage (because monks remain 1-2k hp behind warriors, correct?).<br>
<br>
Furthermore, this circumstance includes that the monk can keep aggro better, long-term, than the warrior can, due to outrageous damage output.  And finally, the monk gets hit less, because block is superior to parry?<br>
<br>
The only data I have seen vis-a-vis block v. parry indicates that block avoids 6% more hits than parry.  So monk avoidance is 6% better, hp are 1k-2k less, damage output is about 150-200% of warriors, and because of damage output, they can maintain aggro well.<br>
<br>
I hope I'm still on track here.  Let me know if I'm wrong about something so far.<br>
<br>
Now, just for some perspective (I'm not asking anything be done, not complaining, just trying to point something out).<br>
<br>
Warrior avoidance skills, according to Frodlin, mean that a warrior avoids 8-11% more hits than a paladin.  Warriors mitigation is just as good as a paladins.  Warriors have 400-1k MORE hp than paladins, and damage output is pretty much a wash, with some claiming paladins hold the high ground, and others claiming the opposite.  Paladins do have the ability to get quick aggro more consistently than warriors.<br>
<br>
Bearing in mind that warriors feel monks are/were better tanks (in some situations) and that warriors feel that paladins are too close to performing as well as warriors, this leads me to believe that the biggest issues warriors feel they face are 1) aggro problems, and 2) damage output.  (ARGH!  I'M BLIND! hehe)<br>
<br>
