<br>
That and the perception that several other classes are constantly being adjusted so that there is less and less of a clear division between them and us.<br>
<br>
We'd like our agro problems adjusted.  We'd prefer taunt be more reliable.  Verant has as much come out and said that isn't going to happen, or at least that's my perception.  We'd also like our damage output to be more in line with was stated by Verant in relation to Monk and Rogue damage output rather than the large jumps in damage they have over us.  I suspect we're not going to see that either.<br>
<br>
And finally, we really don't want to see the Knights upgraded in such a way that you can't really tell a difference between a Knight tanking and a Warrior tanking except where defensive is needed.  Not that Knights should not be able to tank, but once you make them just as effective at it as a Warrior you restrict the need/desire for a Warrior to only raid situations. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/uraluvinssteele.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Raluvin Ssteele</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>knows that Warriors are superior</span><br>  Posts: 90<br> <font color=#FF0000>(10/15/02 7:24:48 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthetavern.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1386.topic&index=115>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: The way I see it</span><hr size=1> Well, I dont wanna rip your point of view to pieces, because in all honesty there are a lot of good points in there and there is a lot of truth.  <br>
<br>
But!!!!!!<br>
<br>
You dont sound like you have played a warrior.  <br>
<br>
I have both a warrior and a monk.  <br>
<br>
Warrior<br>
<br>
Solo'ing forget it!, until I got a Willsapper.  Now I can solo maybe the equivalent of a level 55 character.  I can solo in KC and Velks a little bit, but spend the best part of 20 mins healing.  Fungi or no fungi, its still a lot of hps to restore.  <br>
<br>
But there again, if I was playing, I wouldn't solo.  <br>
<br>
Monks<br>
<br>
Solo'ing is so fecking cake for monks its unbelievable.  Oh your losing ? FD.  Plus that have massive damage mitigation...30% more than warriors ? I cant see this being right.  Where did you get these statistics from ? <br>
<br>
I also managed to level up a monk from 1-51 in 2 weeks with 85lbs on him, no PLing, no going out of the way for buffage, some deaths with sometimes no rez or a 39 rez....and bingo..Job done, I am pulling in PoH/PoF and wherever else.  <br>
<br>
Just going as a pure dmg machine with average equipment on.  <br>
<br>
Throw a Fungi Tunic on a monk and it has massive differences as it would on a warrior.  As a primary puller, a monk with a fungi can wait until their hps go up accordingly.  A warrior with a fungi is relatively useless.  <br>
<br>
Warrior v Monk <br>
<br>
Very different classes with very different roles.  <br>
<br>
Monks atm DO have not one weakness apart from their hps.  However, with the availability of the epic (is it the easiest?), then the monk can quite easily get away with good weapons, s some decent equipment and the rest you dump on resist and HP equipment.  <br>
<br>
The monk class can actually boost up their weakness to make it a strength and yes, a monk can have hps almost compariable to a warrior (obviously a lot of time and effort needs to be input). <br>
<br>
This means that the monk has NOT ONE major weakness.  Attack is excellent, defensive is excellent, hps are excellent and resists are excellent.  Their only slight weakness would be that they cant carry much (so I have my fun using autosplit when a monk is in group).  With equipment also carrying an average expense for monks, they can also get by relatively cheaply. <br>
<br>
With Warriors, we do not have the versatility in benefitting from both attack and defense.  We have to be heavy on AC/HPs most of which is obtained with equipment.  Equipment is MASSIVELY expensive for a warrior.  We are, bar none the most expensive class to run in EQ as we are heavily reliant on it.  <br>
<br>
Our strengths are obviously taking damage, but where we lose out is dmg output (average) and spell capabilities (none).  <br>
<br>
A combination of these and naff disciplines gives warriors a problem definitely post Luclin. <br>
<br>
Conclusion<br>
It is sad that Monks have been nerfed.  I don't like to see any class nerfed (apart from Manaburning wizards - feck em).  Sadly if their role in standard groups is replacing warriors/paladins/SKs I am sorry but nocando.  <br>
<br>
At the end of the day, monks should be looking to fill the Rogues/Rangers/Monks/BST/Shaman/Mage/Necro spots in a group (note: there are usually 2 slots for these in a gruop and 1 for a tank).  They should not be filling in for a tank (SK/Paladin/Warrior).  <br>
<br>
Their role is puller and damage mitigator and like ranger, scraping the bottom of the barrel a tank.  <br>
<br>
At no point should any class whatsoever have total benefits, which I hate to point, monks do which makes them more desirable in groups, more diserable to solo, more diserable for travelling, more diserable for camping. <br>
