EDIT:  actually, warriors need to campaign for SOMETHING to improve damage output now.  On test the Yaulp spells (used by paladins and clerics) have been changed, and now have haste and +atk on them from yaulp 1 (paladins get at level 9).  I see this as being a problem for warriors, since it could conceivably mean that a paladin at level 39 could potentially outdamage a warrior (Yaulp 2 on test has 10% haste, if both wore the same haste item, would 10% more haste for the paladin make up the damage difference?).<br>
<br>
I don't honestly know what really to suggest, although I'm thinking along the lines of an innate boost to ATK, starting around the same time warriors get critical hits (level 12?).  Maybe a boost of a couple points of ATK every 5 levels or so? <br>
<br>
